<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-20T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-20T20:00:00-05:00" n="148" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d148">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5 Submarines/4: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secrtary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chairman of the American Delegation to the
                                London Naval Conference</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-20T20:00:00-05:00">March 20,
                                    1936—8 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>76. Your 143, March 19, 1 p.m.<note n="4" xml:id="d148fn4">Not
                                printed.</note> The President authorizes the American delegates to
                            the London Naval Conference, 1935, to sign a procès-verbal designed to
                            obtain further accessions to the rules of international law concerning
                            submarine warfare to which the United States as well as the United
                            Kingdom and Japan are now expressly committed under the London Naval
                            Treaty of 1930.<note n="5" xml:id="d148fn5">The Department was informed
                                by telegram No. 165, March 25, 10 p.m., from Mr. Davis that the
                                Japanese would not receive instructions in time for them to sign the
                                procès-verbal before the following week (500.A15A5
                                Submarines/11).</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>